Primitive data types in java are
• Boolean: It takes the values true or false.
• Char: It is used to store a single character.
• Byte: In java it is a 8-bit signed two’s complement integer.
• Short: These are the smallest type at only two bytes(16bits).
• Long: This data type is used to store whole numbers from -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807.
• Float and double: float data type is a single-precision 32-bit IEEE754 floating point. It should never be used for precise values,, such as currency. Its default value is 0.0F.
Operators in java can be classified into many types. Some of them are
• Arithmetic operators
• Unary operators
• Assignment operators
• Relational operators
• Logical operators
• Ternary operators
• Bitwise operators
• Shift operators
• Instance of operator
